<h2 id="Syntax">Syntax</h2>

<pre class="twopartsyntaxbox"><a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax" title="CSS/Value_definition_syntax">Formal syntax</a>: <code>[ <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length" title="Possible values: a number followed by'em', 'ex', 'ch', 'rem', 'px', 'cm', 'mm', 'in', 'vh', 'vw', 'vmin', 'vmax', 'pt', 'pc' or 'px', like 3px, 1.5cm, -0.5em or 0">&lt;length&gt;</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Single_bar" title="Single bar: The two entities are optional, but exactly one must be present.">|</a> <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/number" title="">&lt;number&gt;</a> ]{1,4}</code>
</pre>

<pre>border-image-outset: <em>sides</em> <em>                 /* One-value syntax   */</em>  e.g. border-image-outset: 30%; 
border-image-outset: <em>vertical</em> <em>horizontal</em> <em>   /* Two-value syntax   */ </em> e.g. border-image-outset: 10% 30%; 
border-image-outset: <em>top</em> <em>horizontal</em> <em>bottom </em><em> /* Three-value syntax */ </em> e.g. border-image-outset: 30px 30% 45px; 
border-image-outset: <em>top</em> <em>right</em> <em>bottom</em> <em>left </em><em> /* Four-value syntax  */ </em> e.g. border-image-outset: 7px 12px 14px 5px;

border-image-repeat: inherit
</pre>

<h3 id="Values">Values</h3>

<dl><dt><em>sides</em></dt>
 <dd>Is a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a> or a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/percentage" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;percentage&gt;</code></a> of the amount by which the border image area extends beyond the border box in all four directions.</dd>
 <dt><em>horizontal</em></dt>
 <dd>Is a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a> or a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/percentage" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;percentage&gt;</code></a> of the amount by which the border image area extends beyond the border box in both horizontal directions (left and right).</dd>
 <dt><em>vertical</em></dt>
 <dd>Is a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a> or a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/percentage" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;percentage&gt;</code></a> of the amount by which the border image area extends beyond the border box in both vertical directions (top and bottom).</dd>
 <dt><em>top</em></dt>
 <dd>Is a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a> or a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/percentage" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;percentage&gt;</code></a> of the amount by which the border image area extends beyond the border box past its top edge.</dd>
 <dt><em>bottom</em></dt>
 <dd>Is a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a> or a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/percentage" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;percentage&gt;</code></a> of the amount by which the border image area extends beyond the border box past its bottom edge.</dd>
 <dt><em>right</em></dt>
 <dd>Is a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a> or a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/percentage" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;percentage&gt;</code></a> of the amount by which the border image area extends beyond the border box past its right edge.</dd>
 <dt><em>left</em></dt>
 <dd>Is a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/length" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;length&gt;</code></a> or a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/percentage" title="The documentation about this has not yet been written; please consider contributing!"><code>&lt;percentage&gt;</code></a> of the amount by which the border image area extends beyond the border box past its left edge.</dd>
 <dt><code>inherit</code></dt>
 <dd>Is a keyword indicating that all four values are inherited from each parent elements' calculated value.</dd>
</dl>